Sentencas: A La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta(LSCF) cathode modified using nanosized TiO2 was direct prepared on the yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte in an intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: TiO2-modified La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: TiO2 prevents reaction between LSCF and YSZ, which would have formed a SrZrO3 phase.
Titulo: TiO2-modified La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cell with a LSCF-0.25 wt% TiO2 cathode exhibited a current density that was 1.6 times larger than that with a pure LSCF cathode at 0.7 V and 600 degrees C. Electrochemical impedance spectra showed the accelerated incorporation of oxygen anions into the YSZ electrolyte with the TiO2-modified LSCF cathode.
Titulo: TiO2-modified La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The improvement was attributed to the suppressed formation of a non-conductive SrZrO3 layer at the cathode/electrolyte interface.
Titulo: TiO2-modified La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
